The
object
of
this
apparatus
is
to
spread
and
to
replace
in

a
satisfactory
position
a
fragment
of
mandible
displaced
to
the

median
line
on
account
of
a
fracture
with
loss
of
substance
which

extended
from
the
right
to
the
left
cuspid.

A
special
feature
of
this
apparatus
is
provided
by
the
sepa-

rate
action
of
each
sliding
member,
which
makes
possible
the

movement
as
desired
of
the
front
or
the
back
of
the
fragment,

and
to
arrest
the
progress
of
either
end
at
any
desired
point.

OF
APPARATUS.

expansion
device
is
com-

two
oval
wires
i

German

left
end;

space
between
them
being
5
m/m

(3/16"
approx.).
They
must
be
assembled
parallel
one
to
the

other
and
have
a
total
length
of
7
cm.
(2
3/4"
approx.).

assembling
takes
place

a
thick
round

to

(3)

is

Wires
1
and
2,
extension
4
and
gutter
3,
once
assembled,

form
altogether
one
single
piece.

4,

wires
1
and
2

3,
